extendedInfo.description: The Centre for Engineering Leadership and Management and Young Engineers Australia are co-hosts of the 2012 Engineering Leadership Conference (ELC 2012).  This conference is the major biennial professional event in the Australian engineering industry, with over 600 delegates expected to attend.The conference theme is Passing the Baton â Engineering Australia's Future.  Four important sub-themes will be explored, namely Pathways to Leadership, Transitions in Leadership, Leadership in Industry and Engineering a Better Society.Keynote addresses, general paper sessions, workshops and poster presentations will address the above themes, while networking events will provide extraordinary opportunities for professional interaction with industry colleagues.
